  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\n- This happened both on a mainnet node, Lodestar requested so many peers to connect, during that time node received way more aggregate and proof\r\n\r\n<img width=\"821\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-20 at 14 01 51\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/a30baf04-a20c-4876-b7d3-39d4a9d30959\">\r\n\r\n- Also way more beacon block\r\n\r\n<img width=\"794\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-20 at 14 02 14\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/9f9c25cf-3fcf-4015-a623-e773c878d23b\">\r\n\r\n- CPU usage spiked to an unbelievable number\r\n\r\n<img width=\"796\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-20 at 14 04 49\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/1aa6c956-b684-41bf-b31a-8e1825960f94\">\r\n\r\n- Also GC pause time rate\r\n\r\n<img width=\"795\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-20 at 14 05 25\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/897fe0aa-5d8d-44c5-a834-244fe73aee8c\">\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWith maxPeer=55, a node should only request a number of peers less than that\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating system\n\nLinux\n\n### Lodestar version or commit hash\n\nv1.8.0",
